⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Arobynn Hamel
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Arobynn Hamel:M1:a823e3⟧

WHO   — Arobynn Hamel — King of the Assassins
WHAT  — The central villain of The Assassin's Blade — Celaena's master and maker, who rules by debt and devotion, and who answers her defiance with the death of the one boy she loved and her own betrayal to the salt mines.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — The Assassin's Blade & book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because he cannot abide being left or unloved; because possession wears the mask of family; because the surest cage is one the prisoner is taught to call home, and the surest blade is one that believes it chose its own hand.
HOW   — By money, manipulation, and meticulous cruelty — gifts and beatings traded like coin; by holding lives and debts over those he keeps; by ordering a murder and arranging a betrayal while keeping his hands clean and his smile warm.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Everything I gave you, I can take away — and you will still come home to me.

